DURBAN –Two people lost their lives and 13 others were seriously injured after the minibus taxi that they were travelling in overturned near Umzimkhulu in the Harry Gwala district in southern KZN on Saturday. According to Robert McKenzie of KZN Emergency Medical Services the serious crash occurred just before 12 on Saturday. “A minibus has overturned and tragically two people have sustained fatal injuries in this crash,”he said. McKenzie said paramedics from KZN EMS treated 13 people at the scene for critical and serious injuries. He said after the patients were stabilised they were transported to a hospital for continued medical care. Meanwhile, two people were left in a critical condition after  a car and a minibus taxi collided on the N3 Highway near the Pavilion shopping centre in Durban on Friday night. Mobi-Claw 911 spokesperson Mike Myers said their Cyber Control received an activation from a client who had witnessed a horrific accident after 11pm on Friday night.. He said it was alleged that a car travelling the wrong way on the highway, collided head on with a minibus taxi.  “The taxi burst into flames and left victims entrapped in both vehicles,” he said. Myers said the Mobi-Claw 911 Cyber Control immediately broadcast the incident to all necessary services, including ER24 EMS, SAPS, Vema paramedics, metro traffic and fire services. He said all services were quickly on scene, including other ambulance services and vehicle recovery. “Two victims were critically injured and transported to hospital,”said Myers. Mobi-Claw 911 thanked the client for activating his panic button as well as all the services that attended the scene. THE MERCURY